# CODEOWNERS for the spawntree repo
#
# Why this exists: the repo accepts automated PRs from the gitenv-upstream
# subtree-sync flow ("Sync from gitenv main"). Those PRs land changes that
# were already merged into a downstream consumer; they're pre-vetted by
# CI + Devin Review on each side, but the surface area is wide and a
# silent regression could land without a human ever looking.
#
# Combined with a branch protection rule on `main` that requires "Review
# from Code Owners," this file forces a human ack on every PR — automated
# or not — before it merges. See `.github/SETUP.md` for the protection
# rule that makes this enforceable.

# Default owner for everything. Without a `*` line, GitHub treats files
# with no rule as having no owner, and the "Require review from Code
# Owners" branch protection happily lets them through.
* @ziahamza

# Subtree-sync flows touch every package; explicit listings here would
# duplicate the wildcard above. Keep it simple.

# Workflow + repo-config files: only the maintainer touches these,
# regardless of which automated flow opened the PR.
/.github/                @ziahamza
/.changeset/             @ziahamza
/package.json            @ziahamza
/pnpm-workspace.yaml     @ziahamza
